Notebook[{
Cell["19. Boundary Calibration Decision", "Title",ExpressionUUID->"4143023f-a268-4ad3-a0eb-dd3d1fa94bb0"],

Cell["Decision", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"235be2f1-2e86-43f9-b067-525774bf98b3"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Decision A:",
  FontWeight->Bold],
 " boundary class-defined derivation is recovered on the controlled \
split+welded sector under the hypothesis that the diagonal controlled \
ambiguity component acts trivially modulo the chosen boundary null ideal."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"49d0d6cf-b8d7-41ad-833e-1a6fd15f9c30"],

Cell["\<\
This is the strongest conclusion supported by the exact finite-cutoff WL \
lane. \
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"c1168d7a-6556-4920-bb59-6d8919b6e1c4"],

Cell["Why the answer is not stronger", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"c0e6f899-9b52-4780-9395-003046cbcdb4"],

Cell["The sprint also certifies two limitations. ", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"5b2f82da-1d4d-4b97-84ac-3834c3a408e4"],

Cell["\<\
The strict record sector is automatically invariant, but only because the \
induced derivation collapses there.\
\>", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"ea2005c6-97b2-439e-b234-d7a3328df593"],

Cell["\<\
Unsafe controlled families remain operator-visible, so classical ledger \
endpoints alone do not imply full microscopic calibration invariance.\
\>", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"0b1dedee-3efc-4203-b875-f529aedc6b55"],

Cell["What split+welded restriction actually buys", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"3929bb23-6d07-4d22-9c6d-f2d1694aa231"],

Cell["\<\
The exact controlled projection proves that only the diagonal controlled \
ambiguity component can survive on the boundary controlled sector. This is \
the precise gain from the split-note structure. \
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"19023bc8-7636-4869-b7cd-0b4222fe92be"],

Cell["What remains conditional", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"92522924-4b7b-47df-81a8-a64413d4ea23"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The WL sprint does ",
 StyleBox["not",
  FontWeight->Bold],
 " prove that the transported Main/UOM ambiguity subspace automatically \
satisfies the boundary null-ideal condition. It proves that if the diagonal \
controlled ambiguity blocks are null-ideal valued, then calibration \
dependence becomes representational on the controlled boundary quotient while \
the induced derivation can remain nontrivial. "
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"d87d669c-6d57-4dec-8771-a82ee344da80"],

Cell["Main-facing sentence", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"51f2518d-a641-4262-992a-c69fd59da968"],

Cell["\<\
Boundary class-defined derivation is recovered on the controlled split+welded \
sector under a diagonal-controlled-ambiguity null-ideal hypothesis; without \
that hypothesis, visible controlled countermodels remain, so selector \
pressure is still real. \
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"1d12fa20-21c9-4712-93a1-a1b723438d9a"],

Cell["Status", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"28525c6f-59d4-456c-a17f-eb6be0f9d421"],

Cell[BoxData[
 PaneBox[
  PaneBox[
   StyleBox[
    TagBox[
     TagBox[GridBox[{
        {
         TagBox["\<\"Decision lane\"\>",
          HoldForm], 
         TagBox["\<\"Status\"\>",
          HoldForm]},
        {"\<\"Exact strict-record trivialization theorem\"\>", \
"\<\"finite-dimensional-theorem-certificate\"\>"},
        {"\<\"Exact controlled reduction theorem\"\>", \
"\<\"finite-dimensional-theorem-certificate\"\>"},
        {"\<\"Exact nontrivial mod-null invisible controlled family\"\>", "\<\
\"finite-dimensional-theorem-certificate\"\>"},
        {"\<\"Exact visible controlled countermodel\"\>", \
"\<\"finite-dimensional-theorem-certificate\"\>"},
        {"\<\"Final sprint decision: conditional Path A, not automatic \
invariance\"\>", "\<\"finite-dimensional-theorem-certificate\"\>"}
       },
       GridBoxAlignment->{
        "Columns" -> {Center, {Center}}, "Rows" -> {{Baseline}}},
       GridBoxDividers->{
        "Columns" -> {{False}}, "Rows" -> {False, True, {False}, False}},
       GridBoxSpacings->{"Columns" -> {
           Offset[0.27999999999999997`], {
            Offset[2.0999999999999996`]}, 
           Offset[0.27999999999999997`]}, "Rows" -> {
           Offset[0.2], {
            Offset[0.4]}, 
           Offset[0.2]}}],
      {None, OutputFormsDump`HeadedColumns}],
     Function[BoxForm`e$, 
      TableForm[
      BoxForm`e$, TableHeadings -> {None, {"Decision lane", "Status"}}]]], 
    "Text",
    StripOnInput->False,
    ShowStringCharacters->False],
   ImageMargins->{{0, 0}, {5, 5}}],
  ImageMargins->{{0, 0}, {5, 5}}]], "TextTableForm", \
"Text",ExpressionUUID->"ce3afc8f-2f12-4f2d-9e40-e62ff35a8b41"]
},
